Should You Switch to IDURAR?
NO - Here's why:

Indian Compliance Missing: IDURAR doesn't have GST, FSSAI, or Indian tax compliance built-in. You'd need to heavily customize it.

No Inventory Management: IDURAR is focused on invoicing/CRM, not inventory. Your FMCG business needs batch tracking and warehouse management.

Deployment Complexity: IDURAR requires MongoDB Atlas (cloud) or self-hosted MongoDB, which increases costs and complexity.

Your Current System Works: Mohi ERP already has the core features you need with Indian compliance. It's better to enhance it than start over.

Learning Curve: Your team would need to learn React, Node.js, and MongoDB to maintain IDURAR.

Best Path Forward
Keep Mohi ERP and selectively adopt IDURAR's best practices:

